<dl id="n35258a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35258a">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35258a"> 258(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hair of the / old dog</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> As the result of his attendance at the feast he was drunk that night and sick in the morning, when the remedy of a &ldquo;hair of the old dog,&rdquo; otherwise a glass of neat whisky, was suggested. <small> J. Fitzgerald Molloy, <a name="JFMR2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JFMR2"><cite title="source">The Romance of the Irish Stage</cite></a> (1897) II 82</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
